bug.short_desc: kernel 4.5.0-0.rc7.git0.2.fc24 doesn't boot on Banana Pi

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1137383 screenshot of u-boot
Description of problem: Using image Fedora-Minimal-armhfp-24_Alpha-5-sda.raw.xz (Fedora 24 Alpha 1.5), I'm unable to boot on Banana Pi. All I get is "Starting kernel ..." in u-boot.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
kernel 4.5.0-0.rc7.git0.2.fc24 u-boot 2016.03-rc3
Steps to Reproduce: 1. download Fedora 24 Alpha 1.5 arm image (from [1]) 2. $ fedora-arm-image-installer --media=/dev/mmcblk0 --target=Bananapi --image=Fedora-Minimal-armhfp-24_Alpha-5-sda.raw.xz 3. insert into Banana Pi and boot.
Actual results: Fedora doesn't boot.
Expected results: Fedora boots.
[1] https://kojipkgs.fedoraproject.org/compose/24/Fedora-24-20160316.3/compose/Spins/armhfp/images/Fedora-Minimal-armhfp-24_Alpha-5-sda.raw.xz

Proposed as a Freeze Exception for 24-alpha by Fedora user pbrobinson using the blocker tracking app because:
The uboot-tools-2016.03-3 build fixes booting for a number of AllWinner ARM devices. It would be good to have this accepted as a FE, the patches added are self contained and straight forward so there's minimal risk to other ARMv7 devices, and it doesn't impact other architectures.
uboot-tools-2016.03-3.fc24 has been submitted as an update to Fedora 24. https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2016-bdd2592ee5
+1 FE, targeted hardware enablement is worthwhile.
